Example: "Cubed Sphere Simulation with Seasonal Forcing"
=======================================

Build:

To apply the changes to the default configuration of MITgcmUV:
Configure and compile the code:
  cd verification/global_ocean.cubed32x32x30/build
  ../../../tools/genmake -mods=../code -enable=therm_seaice -enable=bulk_force -fc=ifc
  make depend
  make

To run the code:
  cd verification/global_ocean.cubed32x32x30/run
  ln -s ../input/* .
  ../build/mitgcmuv

There is comparison output in directory:
 ../verification/global_ocean.cubed32x32x30/results

Experiments:
  Exp1 - 1 year run, spin-up from rest




=======================================
Notes:  To disable bulk forcing and sea ice,
go to data.pkg and set
 useBulkforce=.FALSE.,
 useThermSeaIce=.FALSE.,




=======================================
Scripts:

Input forcing fields:
  ncep2cube.m  - creates forcing fields from NCEP monthly climatology
  ncep2cubeWind.m  - creates forcing fields from NCEP monthly climatology
                     for bulk forcing (wind speed on tracer points)
  


Output analysis:
  plot_psi.m - computes and plots overturning stream function
  plot_ts.m  - plots surface T and S

